  {
    "pid": "obj6",
    "creator": "Priscella Vega",
    "location": "Los Angeles Times",
    "label": "Elizabeth ‘Betita’ Martínez, prolific author and pioneering Chicana, dies",
    "_date": "6/29/2021",
    "object_type": "text",
    "current_location": "Los Angeles Times",
    "excerpt": "She became the founding editor of El Grito del Norte, a pioneering community newspaper that documented the struggles of Hispanos and Mexicans reclaiming land grants from the U.S. government. She taught women how to write stories, encouraged travel to educational conferences and instilled unity among them. Their work gained national recognition from luminaries such as Talamante.",
    "collection": "martinez",
    "thumbnail": "",
    "permalink": "/martinez/obj6",
