  {
    "pid": "obj9",
    "creator": "Erik Wallenberg",
    "location": "Monthly Review",
    "label": "Standing Against Racism and Empire: Remembering Elizabeth \"Betita\" Sutherland Martinez",
    "_date": "4/5/2002",
    "object_type": "text",
    "current_location": "Monthly Review",
    "excerpt": "Elizabeth 'Betita' Sutherland Martinez spent her life fighting the death and destruction imposed by the White House and the Pentagon, from border jails to police barracks in every city and town across the United States. She used her powers as a gifted translator, editor, author, and organizer in opposition to racism and the brutality of empire building, and in agitation for an alternative society. ",
